core.CourseUserInfo.description:
An API-safe representation of a course user.
Embed the BaseUserInfo and use CourseUserInfoType as the type.

core.EnrollmentInfo.description: An API-safe representation of enrollment information.

core.ServerUserInfo.description:
An API-safe representation of a server user.
Embed the BaseUserInfo and use ServerUserInfoType as the type.

core.TargetCourseUser.description:
A request having a field of this type indicates that the request is targeting a specific course user.
This type serializes to/from a string.
A user's email must be specified, but no error is generated if the user is not found.
The existence of this type in a struct also indicates that the request is at least a APIRequestCourseUserContext.

core.TargetCourseUserSelfOrGrader.description:
Same as TargetServerUserSelfOrAdmin, but in the context of a course user and a grader context user.
Therefore, the context user only has to be a grader in the context course (or the target user themself).
When targeting yourself, the user can be a server admin (and will be escalated to course owner for the request).
The existence of this type in a struct also indicates that the request is at least a APIRequestCourseUserContext.

core.TargetServerUser.description:
A request having a field of this type indicates that the request is targeting a specific server user.
This type serializes to/from a string.
A user's email must be specified, but no error is generated if the user is not found.
The existence of this type in a struct also indicates that the request is at least a APIRequestUserContext.

core.TargetServerUserSelfOrAdmin.description:
A request having a field of this type indicates that the request is targeting a specific user.
This type serializes to/from a string.
If no user is specified, then the context user is the target.
If a user is specified, then the context user must be a server admin
(any user can access their own resources, but higher permissions are required to access another user's resources).
No error is generated if the user is not found.
The existence of this type in a struct also indicates that the request is at least a APIRequestUserContext.

model.ExternalLocatableError.description:
A user safe version of locatable errors.
All LocatableErrors must be converted to ExternalLocatableErrors
if it is to be given to a user.

model.ExternalScoringInfo.description: A trimmed-down version of ScoringInfo meant for external usage.

model.ExternalUserOpResult.description:
A user safe representation of the UserOpResult struct.
Notably all errors will be converted to responses and the cleartext password field is removed.
For descriptions of shared fields, see UserOpResult above.

model.LocatableError.description: A general representation of errors that have a definite source location.

model.RawCourseUserData.description:
Raw/dirty data for a course user.
This struct is used for raw data coming from a single course.

model.RawServerUserData.description:
Raw/dirty data for a user.
This struct can be directly embedded for Kong arguments.

model.UserOpResult.description:
A general representation of the result of operations that modify a user in any way (add, remove, enroll, drop, etc).
All user-facing functions (essentially non-db functions) should return an instance or collection of these objects.
